'''Japanification''' is a [[derogatory]] term used to describe the process of becoming or wishing to become a fully integrated member of the [[Japan]]ese community. It most commonly refers to [[ex-pat]]s living for an extended period of time in Japan, though it may also be used to describe persons living outside Japan who have a certain affinity to some aspect of [[Japanese culture]]. Adoption of Japanese mannerisms, style of clothing, taste in entertainment, and sometimes aspects of [[Japanese language]] may be most evident.

In ex-pats this process often occurs because of a feeling of isolation or desire to conform, whereas outside Japan it may occur because of an especially strong interest in some kind of fan culture based in Japan (for example [[anime]], [[lolita|lolita  style]], [[J-pop]], etc.)

